Diff between c/c++/java vs python:
----------------------------------------
---> no main method
--->  .py ==> python file or python module
----> a python file contains:
      global code
      global variables
      global methods
      class ----> (varibles + methods)
-----> python ==  procedural + object oriented
-----> python is scripting + programming lang
-----> c/c++/java ----> 1st compilation then execution
          1. compilation ---> compile all 100 lines
          2. execution ---> execute each and every line
-----> python ----> compilation + execute happens for evety line at smae time
         1. compile line and execute line immediately          
-----> python is an expression/ easy language
-----> Python is a type less language
no need to spevify data type

          







